-- Indonesia Stock Movers: Adaro Energy, Medco Energi, Semen Gresik
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2011-12-19T09:15:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/indonesia-stocks-movers-adaro-energy-bumi-resources-medco.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (JCI)  moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices as of the close in Jakarta.  The Jakarta Composite index rose 0.1 percent to 3,770.29.  Coal producers:  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI)  , Asia’s biggest
exporter of power-station coal, fell 2.2 percent to 2,200 rupiah
and  PT Adaro Energy (ADRO)  , Indonesia’s second-largest coal
producer, lost 2.7 percent to 1,790 rupiah. Power-station coal
 prices  at Australia’s Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark,
declined 1.1 percent to $110.28 a metric ton in the week ended
Dec. 16.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC)  , Indonesia’s
largest listed oil company, climbed 1 percent to 2,475 rupiah. A
unit of the company obtained approval to “commercially”
develop the Area 47 oil field in  Libya , Medco said. Medco and
its partners will build an oil production plant with a capacity
of 50,000 barrels a day within the next 36 months, it said.  PT Semen Gresik (SMGR)  , the nation’s biggest cement
producer, gained 4.8 percent to 10,850 rupiah, closing at a
record. The shares rose on expectations Semen Gresik’s cement
sales will improve after the parliament passed last week a land
acquisition bill and as the company’s new plants start operating
next year, said Gifar Indra Sakti, an analyst at PT Sucorinvest
Central Gani.  To contact the reporter on this story:
